The first two Magma albums are basically free jazzy fusion. The MDK/Kohntarkosz are far more minimal, and there used to be a performance of them doing MDK with just one keyboard, bass, drums, and a single singer.
They got trippier as the 70's went on.

Most prog-ish bands are afraid to play with their own material, but revival era Magma is fun to see how they'll rework a piece. An example is they redid this cycle as a vocal piece with really minimal instrumentation. Stripped it down to ~ 40 minutes of doomy chanting.

And I swear I've heard NoMeansNo before.
I love the whole explosion of late 80s to 2000ish technical ability in punk/metal. Jazzy in a crazy way, kind of a fuck the limits mentality.
Definitely something for later, so thanks in return.
